  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Start cooking the chorizo</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 minutes or until starting to crisp.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>onions</strong></span>.</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong>. Boil a kettle.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1512.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1512.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1512.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1512.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1512.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare your saffron stock </strong></p>\n<p>Once the chorizo is starting to crisp, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes further or until the onion has softened.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 800ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.6L]</span> <strong>boiled water, </strong>add the <strong>saffron</strong> and set aside to infuse – this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>",
