      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the grape &amp; chicory salad</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>grapes</strong> in half.</p>\n<p>Separate the <strong>chicory leaves </strong>until you're just left with the <strong>core</strong>. Cut the <strong>core</strong> into quarters.</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil </strong>in a bowl. Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and mix well until combined – this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong>.</p>",
